  "timeframe": "1H",
  "market_context": "After a bullish break of structure and pullback into a discount zone with FVG/Order Block confluence, price aggressively sold off during New York session, breaking the prior swing low that had been controlling higher highs.",
  "key_observation": "The break of the structural low—previously used to confirm new higher highs—invalidated the bullish bias and confirmed a Change of Character (CHoCH) to bearish.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified prior swing high and low, then marked a bullish Break of Structure (BOS) upward followed by a pullback into a discount zone with FVG and order block confluence.",
    "Step 2: Waited for price to enter the confluence zone and looked for lower-timeframe bullish shift (e.g., aggressive move at London open) to confirm long setup.",
    "Step 3: Observed aggressive sell-off in New York session that broke the key swing low previously used to validate higher highs, signaling a Change of Character (CHoCH).",
    "Step 4: Reassessed market structure: now bearish with lower high and lower low; identified new premium/discount using Asia session range and aligned with IFVG and order block.",
    "Step 5: Waited for price to re-enter the bearish confluence zone on 1-minute chart, then required confirmation via break of the new swing low before entering short.",
    "Step 6: Executed short trade on 1-minute order block with stop above the high, targeting the M15 swing low; applied partial profit at 5R (50% position) and let remainder run to full target."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade executed short after CHoCH confirmation; 50% position closed at 5R, remainder targeted at ~9.6R; aggressive downside move occurred during New York session confirming success.",
  "lessons": "Never cling to a bias when price breaks a key structural level; CHoCH must be respected immediately. Refining entries using lower-timeframe confirmation within confluence zones improves risk-reward and win rate.",
